h state and the exploitation of its inhabitants. During Nazi occupation, previously unimagined assets were expropriated, redistributed, or simply stolen to achieve the goals of Germanization policy and the wartime economy. The tax and customs administrations were actively involved in this system of injustice.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 10. Jan 2022) 4aAusbeutung. 4aBesatzung Polens. 4aPlünderung. 4aReichsfinanzministerium. 4aZweiter Weltkrieg. 7aHISTORY / Europe / Germany.2bisacsh  aPlundering.  aReich Finance Ministry.  aSecond World War.  aexploitation.  aoccupation of Poland.1 aCaplan, Jane, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2022 Part 1z97831107668200 cEPUBz97831107180890 cprintz978311071793840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311071802740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110718027423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110718027/original  a978-3-11-076682-0  DG Plus DeG Package 2022 Part 1b2022  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_CL_LAEC  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA5EBK